I have added a Windows binary installer for the latest version of 
Cantera (1.5.3).  It contains the Python interface, MATLAB toolbox, 
demos for both, and some documentation. (If you are interested in using 
Cantera from C++ or Fortran, get the source distribution instead.) 
Everything should install and run without errors - if you do find a 
problem, please let me know.

  The installer is file Cantera153.msi at the usual SourceForge site.


Dave Goodwin
